title.narrative: Improving Production&Market Capacity of Smallholder Fruit&Vegetable Farmers in Southern Africa

description.narrative: The Horticulture project in Mozambique, South Africa, Zambia and Zimbabwe, aims to support local food systems by combining production of different fruits and vegetables, crop rotation and restored and improved soil fertility. By the end of 2021, we have supported 11,598 producers and 4,646 producers have increased earnings from accessing a wider range of markets, as well as high value markets. In addition, the producers have reduced their production costs.
